    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1990-05-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1990-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="114"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d114">
                <head>114. Memorandum From <persName corresp="#p_SJ_1">Jeffrey Starr</persName> of
                    the Delegation to the Nuclear and Space Talks in Geneva to the Arms Control and
                    Disarmament Agency (<persName corresp="#p_LRF_1">Lehman</persName>)<note n="1"
                        type="source" xml:id="d114fn1">Source: Department of State, Verification,
                        Compliance and Implementation, Lot 06D436, Verification, Compliance and
                        Implementation Subject Files, 1983–2005, Ministerials: Washington April 4–6
                        1990. Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1990-05-09"
                            >May 9, 1990</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Outstanding START Issues</item>
                </list>
                <p>As requested, attached is the list of 32 issues which the Secretary and the
                    Soviet Foreign Minister agreed in April to attempt to resolve in Geneva before
                    the next ministerial. You should be aware also that Ambassadors <persName
                        corresp="#p_BRR_1">Burt</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_NY_1"
                        >Nazarkin</persName> have agreed to expand the 32 issues list to 50 issues.
                    The Delegation has drawn up a list of additional issues and will begin
                    discussions with the Soviets tomorrow on it. There is no formal list of issues,
                    internal or agreed, to be resolved by the time of the summit; in fact, there has
                    been some reluctance to draw up such a list. Nonetheless, a list of other
                    outstanding <gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss> issues is attached.</p>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <note rend="inline">
                        <hi rend="strong">Attachment</hi>
                    </note>
                    <head>Paper Prepared in the Delegation to the Nuclear and Space Talks in
                            Geneva<note n="2" xml:id="d114fn2">Secret.</note>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian">undated</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p rend="center">32 ISSUES</p>
                    <p rend="center">As Agreed by The Secretary and The Soviet Foreign Minister at
                        the April Ministerial in Washington</p>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Definition of new types of strategic offensive arms</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Warhead attribution for future types of ballistic missiles</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Basing terminology</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>Sublimits on mobile <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">ICBM</gloss> launchers
                            and on warheads on mobile <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">ICBM</gloss>s</item>
                        <pb facs="0701" n="674" xml:id="pg_674"/>
                        <label>5.</label>
                        <item>Launchers on newly constructed submarines which have not yet begun sea
                            trials</item>
                        <label>6.</label>
                        <item>Phasing of reductions of strategic offensive arms</item>
                        <label>7.</label>
                        <item>Provisions regarding initial accountability under the treaty</item>
                        <label>8.</label>
                        <item>Prohibition on rapid reload</item>
                        <label>9.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_CHF_1">Cooper</persName>ative measures to assist
                            National Technical Means</item>
                        <label>10.</label>
                        <item>Restrictions on test and training launchers</item>
                        <label>11.</label>
                        <item>Telemetry issues: data exchange, exemptions from the encapsulation
                            ban, signal strength</item>
                        <label>12.</label>
                        <item>Strategic R&amp;D boosters</item>
                        <label>13.</label>
                        <item>Questions related to mobile <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">ICBM</gloss>s,
                            including basing areas, categories of movements and verification</item>
                        <label>14.</label>
                        <item>Launchers on submarines undergoing overhaul and conversion</item>
                        <label>15.</label>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">ICBM</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_SLBM_1"
                                >SLBM</gloss> warhead sublimits</item>
                        <label>16.</label>
                        <item>Perimeter/Portal Continuous Monitoring, including the establishment
                            thereof</item>
                        <label>17.</label>
                        <item>Suspect-site inspection</item>
                        <label>18.</label>
                        <item>New kinds: <gloss target="#t_ASBM_1">ASBM</gloss>s, ICCMs</item>
                        <label>19.</label>
                        <item>Use of the terms “produce” and “develop”</item>
                        <label>20.</label>
                        <item>Non-deployment of strategic offensive arms beyond the national
                            territory and verification thereof</item>
                        <label>21.</label>
                        <item>Vehicles for launching objects into the upper atmosphere or space, and
                            limitations on the use of such vehicles</item>
                        <label>22.</label>
                        <item>Non-deployed missiles and the conversion or elimination of such
                            missiles</item>
                        <label>23.</label>
                        <item>Non-circumvention</item>
                        <label>24.</label>
                        <item>Duration</item>
                        <label>25.</label>
                        <item>Support equipment</item>
                        <label>26.</label>
                        <item>Throw-weight</item>
                        <label>27.</label>
                        <item>Unique identifiers</item>
                        <label>28.</label>
                        <item>Pre-inspection movement restrictions</item>
                        <label>29.</label>
                        <item>Definition of “inspection site”</item>
                        <label>30.</label>
                        <item>Precision of coordinates in the MOU</item>
                        <label>31.</label>
                        <item>Procedures for inspection before destruction of missiles in
                            canisters</item>
                        <label>32.</label>
                        <item>Restructuring of the Inspection Protocol</item>
                    </list>
                </frus:attachment>
                <pb facs="0702" n="675" xml:id="pg_675"/>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <note rend="inline">
                        <hi rend="strong">Attachment</hi>
                    </note>
                    <head>Paper Prepared in the Delegation to the Nuclear and Space Talks in
                            Geneva<note n="3" xml:id="d114fn3">Secret.</note>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian">undated</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p rend="center">OUTSTANDING START ISSUES NOT ON 32 ISSUES LIST</p>
                    <p rend="sectiontitleital">Major Issues</p>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_ALCM_1">ALCM</gloss>s</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_SLCM_1">SLCM</gloss>s</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Follow-on negotiations</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>Heavy <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">ICBM</gloss>s</item>
                    </list>
                    <p rend="sectiontitleital">Other Issues</p>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Heavy bomber definiton</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Former heavy bomber definition</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Elimination of warheads</item>
                    </list>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
